summary: Towards Infinity - LadyAriadna - Iron Man (Movies), Marvel Cinematic Universe, Spider-Man: Homecoming (2017), The Avengers...
title: Towards Infinity - LadyAriadna - Iron Man (Movies), Marvel Cinematic Universe, Spider-Man: Homecoming (2017), The Avengers (Marvel Movies) [Archive of Our Own]
excerpt: An Archive of Our Own, a project of the Organization for Transformative Works
description:
We were never shown how Tony Stark and Peter Parker grew closer prior to the events of Infinity War. To fill this gap, This series is of one-shots/stories between Spider-Man: Homecoming and Avengers: Infinity War.

Most of these are based on head canons I have or those I read that I think could fit in canon (the movies, theories and the supporting MCU comic tie-ins). Inspiration may also come from the main Marvel Comic Universe (Earth 616) and other materials such as novels.

*** This series is Team Cap friendly. ***

Series Status: Incomplete

The stories so far:

1. Thank You

It’s been two days since May Parker found out about Spider-man and Tony was surprised. He’s not the only one keeping a secret.

2. The Grand Tour

Peter was beyond excited when Tony Stark asked to meet up after school. Instead of a mission as Peter expected, Tony Stark took him somewhere more awesome.

3. From the Outside, Looking In

Stories of Tony and Peter’s father-son relationship from the perspective of the people around them.

4. The Queen Incident

What is “The Queen Incident” Rhodey mentioned in Chapter 5 of From the Outside, Looking In?

5. The Spidey Training Montage

Peter stayed at the Avengers compound during the midwinter break. Tony and Rhodey planned to use the time to extensively train him. He thought he already learned enough from over two years of being Spider-man. He was wrong.

Stories 6 - 8 still in the works.

summary: Spidey is not above letting his emotions overcome him and punching an ally in the face out of the blue, even out of any combat...
body:
Spidey is not above letting his emotions overcome him and punching an ally in the face out of the blue, even out of any combat situation.

He once decked Captain America because he knew that Flash Thompson was Venom and hadn’t told Peter. With his deep-rooted hatred of Venom and Flash being his friend, Spidey really didn’t take the news well (1).

There is a second example when Peter became CEO of Parker industry. He randomly met Iron Man as Spidey and Tony, unaware of Peter’s secret identity, kept dissing his company to his face. Spidey hit him square in the face (2).

(Source : (1) Amazing Spider-man vol.3 #2, (2) Amazing Spider-man vol.4 #13)
